        "content": "200-Amp Panel Upgrade: $3,200 - $4,800\nStandard rural home upgrade includes premium panel with 40-42 circuit spaces, service entrance upgrades, enhanced grounding for desert soil conditions, whole-home surge protection, permitting and inspections, and utility coordination. Higher costs apply when significant trenching or service entrance relocation required.\n\n400-Amp Service Upgrade: $5,500 - $6,800\nLarge rural properties with multiple outbuildings, solar systems, EV chargers, and heavy equipment loads require 400-amp service. Includes dual 200-amp panels or single 400-amp panel, upgraded utility transformer (if needed), extensive grounding system, commercial-grade surge protection, and comprehensive permitting.\n\nWell Pump Electrical Installation/Repair: $1,200 - $3,500\nDedicated 30-amp circuit from panel to well, proper wire sizing for distance (often 200-400 feet), control box installation and wiring, surge protection (critical for lightning-prone desert), pressure switch and controls, troubleshooting existing systems, and emergency repairs. Cost varies with distance from panel to well, depth of well (affects pump HP), and underground trenching requirements.\n\nWhole-Home Generator Installation: $8,500 - $18,000\nComplete installation includes generator unit (14-24kW typical for rural homes), automatic transfer switch, concrete pad and installation, gas line or propane connection, electrical connections and testing, permitting and inspections, and startup and training. Cost depends on generator size (kW rating), fuel type (natural gas vs. propane), transfer switch complexity (protecting well pump and critical circuits), and distance from panel to installation location.\n\nBarn/Workshop Sub-Panel Installation: $2,400 - $5,500\n100-amp sub-panel with 24-30 circuit spaces, trenched underground electrical feed (100-200 feet typical), proper conduit and wire sizing, disconnect switch at building, GFCI protection as required, permits and inspections, and initial circuit installation. Cost increases with distance from main panel, rocky soil conditions requiring extensive trenching, and number of initial circuits installed.\n\nLevel 2 EV Charger Installation: $1,200 - $2,800\n40-50 amp dedicated circuit from panel, proper outdoor-rated wiring and conduit, NEMA 14-50 outlet or hardwired charger, mounting and placement, permitting (if required), and testing. Cost depends on distance from panel to charging location, panel capacity (may require panel upgrade), and charger type (outlet vs. hardwired vs. Tesla Wall Connector).\n\nUnderground Service Run (Per 100 Feet): $800 - $1,600\nTrenched conduit installation, appropriate wire sizing for distance and load, junction boxes and pull points, proper burial depth and marking, inspection and backfill, and desert landscaping restoration. Cost affected by soil conditions (caliche rock common in Avra Valley), obstacles requiring boring rather than trenching, and depth requirements."
