        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Strategic charger placement minimizes installation costs while ensuring convenient, safe operation for years to come.\n\nIdeal Charger Location Considerations:\n- Proximity to Panel: Every 100 feet from panel adds $400-800 to installation (wire and conduit costs)\n- Vehicle Parking Position: Charger should reach vehicle charge port without cable strain (typical charging cables 18-25 feet)\n- Weather Protection: Avra Valley's intense sun and monsoon rains affect outdoor equipment longevity\n- Security: Rural properties may want charger in secured area\n- Future Flexibility: Consider property changes, additional vehicles, resale value\n\nElectrical Routing Options:\n- Direct Interior Route: Shortest distance through garage or utility room (lowest cost)\n- Exterior Conduit: Running conduit along building exterior to outdoor charger location\n- Underground Trench: Required for separated structures or distant parking areas (adds $800-1,600 per 100 feet)\n- Obstacle Avoidance: Plan around well equipment, septic systems, landscaping, underground utilities\n\nRural Property Specific Considerations:\n- Multiple Parking Areas: Rural properties often have vehicle parking at house, barn, workshop\n- RV/Trailer Charging: Some rural owners want EV charger to also serve RVs or electric equipment\n- Dust and Debris: Avra Valley dust requires weather-tight electrical enclosures\n- Animals and Pests: Conduit protects wiring from rodents common in rural areas\n\nProfessional Site Assessment: During free consultation, our electricians walk your property evaluating optimal routing, measuring distances, identifying obstacles, and recommending cost-effective solutions specific to your rural property layout."
