        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Rural Avra Valley properties often served by Trico Electric Cooperative may have limitations on total service capacity requiring utility coordination.\n\nCheck Utility Service Details:\n- Identify your utility provider (Trico Electric Cooperative or TEP)\n- Determine your current service rating (100A, 200A, or 400A)\n- Verify service type (overhead or underground)\n- Check transformer capacity (shared transformers on rural properties may limit upgrades)\n\nWhen Utility Upgrades May Be Required:\n- Upgrading from 100A to 200A service for EV charging and panel capacity\n- Adding EV charger to property already near service capacity\n- Properties with shared transformers (neighboring properties affect capacity)\n- Older rural services with deteriorated utility connections\n\nUtility Coordination Process:\n- We Handle This For You: Intelligent Design coordinates all utility requirements\n- Submit service upgrade applications to Trico or TEP\n- Schedule utility infrastructure upgrades if needed\n- Coordinate timing between utility work and electrical installation\n- Ensure all utility requirements met before final inspection\n\nTimeline Considerations:\n- Standard EV charger installation: 1-3 days from approval to completion\n- Projects requiring utility service upgrade: add 2-4 weeks for utility scheduling\n- Panel upgrade + utility coordination: 3-5 weeks total timeline\n- We provide accurate timeline estimates during free assessment\n\nCost Implications:\n- Utility service upgrades: typically $400-1,200 (utility charges, not our fees)\n- Underground service upgrades may cost more than overhead\n- Transformer upgrades on rural properties (if required): $800-2,500\n- We include all costs in comprehensive written estimate"
